      "id": "tradeoffs",
      "durationMs": 32500,
      "narration": {
        "text": "The main detail to keep in mind is that the runtime still expects the same implementation naming convention. So if you implement the class in Swift, you should keep the generated implementation name and annotate it with @objc(...) so the runtime can discover it properly."
